subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caml
object: Caml (originally an acronym for Categorical Abstract Machine Language) is a multi-paradigm, general-purpose programming language which is a dialect of the ML programming language family. Caml was developed in France at INRIA and ENS. Caml is statically typed, strictly evaluated, and uses automatic memory management. OCaml, the main descendant of Caml, adds many features to the language, including an object layer.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caml
object: CAML (Categorical Abstract Machine Language)  una versione del linguaggio di programmazione ML sviluppata in Francia presso l'INRIA e l'cole Normale Suprieure (ENS). La sua prima implementazione, in Lisp,  stata soprannominata Heavy CAML per la richiesta di ingenti risorse computazionali in confronto al suo successore CAML Light, implementato in C da Xavier Leroy and Damien Doligez. Oltre alla completa riscrittura, CAML Light aggiunge al precedente nucleo del linguaggio un potente sistema di modularizzazione.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Behavioral_Description_Language
object: Behavioral Description Language (BDL) is a programming language based on ANSI C with extensions for hardware description, developed to describe hardware at levels ranging from the algorithm level to the functional level. Although the term Behavioral Description Language is a generic term and can refer to multiple high-level description languages, NEC Corporation has developed a C-subset called BDL for High-Level Synthesis. This C-subset includes its own data types (called var-class), special constants for hardware design e.g. high impedance, timing descriptors and control statements.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing  uma linguagem de programao de cdigo aberto e ambiente de desenvolvimento integrado (IDE), construdo para as artes eletrnicas e comunidades de projetos visuais com o objetivo de ensinar noes bsicas de programao de computador em um contexto visual e para servir como base para cadernos eletrnicos. O projeto foi iniciado em 2001 por e , ambos ex-membros do Grupo de Computao do MIT Media Lab. Um dos objetivos do Processing  atuar como uma ferramenta para no-programadores iniciados com a programao, atravs da satisfao imediata com um retorno visual. A linguagem tem por base as capacidades grficas da linguagem de programao Java, simplificando caractersticas e criar alguns novos.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing is a free graphical library and integrated development environment (IDE) built for the electronic arts, new media art, and visual design communities with the purpose of teaching non-programmers the fundamentals of computer programming in a visual context. Processing uses the Java language, with additional simplifications such as additional classes and aliased mathematical functions and operations. It also provides a graphical user interface for simplifying the compilation and execution stage.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/PureBasic
object: PureBasic is a commercially distributed procedural computer programming language and integrated development environment based on BASIC and developed by for Windows, Linux, and macOS. An Amiga version is available, although it has been discontinued and some parts of it are released as open-source. The first public release of PureBasic for Windows was on 17 December 2000. It has been continually updated ever since.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/PureBasic
object:
PureBasic est un langage de programmation de type BASIC compil. Plusieurs points le caractrisent : 
* Simplicit : la syntaxe BASIC est simple  apprendre. 
* Rapidit : les applications produites sont optimises (taille rduite) et rapides. 
* Portabilit : le code source est portable d'un systme d'exploitation  l'autre. Il existe une version de PureBasic pour Linux, Windows, AmigaOS, et Mac OS. 
* Sans dpendances logicielles : le langage ainsi que les applications ne ncessitent pas d'installation obligatoire, il est donc ais de le transporter sur une cl USB, et d'excuter les applications sous forme d'applications portables. 
* Cration de fichiers DLL : la cration de DLL standard (Non ActiveX, utilisable dans n'importe quel autre langage) est aussi aise que la cration d'EXE.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/PureBasic
object: PureBasic, ontwikkeld door Frdric Laboureur (Fantaisie Software, Frankrijk), is een commercile compiler voor Windows, Linux, AmigaOS en Mac OS. De programma's zijn klein en snel, de syntaxis een mix tussen BASIC en C. Naast de vele krachtig geoptimaliseerde bibliotheken (GUI-gadgets, beeld, geluid, netwerk, database, compressie, cryptografie, ....) kan men rechtstreeks WinAPI aanspreken en Assembler-code gebruiken (Inline-Assembler). Bovendien is het mogelijk om een bibliotheek te schrijven. Verder biedt PureBasic sinds versie 3.5 een basale 3D-engine (OGRE 3D), waarmee het mogelijk is snel en eenvoudig kleine 3-D toepassingen te programmeren. subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python is a high-level, general-purpose programming language. Its design philosophy emphasizes code readability with the use of significant indentation. Python is dynamically-typed and garbage-collected. It supports multiple programming paradigms, including structured (particularly procedural), object-oriented and functional programming. It is often described as a "batteries included" language due to its comprehensive standard library. Python consistently ranks as one of the most popular programming languages.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python  un linguaggio di programmazione di "alto livello", orientato a oggetti, adatto, tra gli altri usi, a sviluppare applicazioni distribuite, scripting, computazione numerica e system testing. Ideato da Guido van Rossum all'inizio degli anni novanta,  spesso paragonato a Ruby, Tcl, Perl, JavaScript, Visual Basic o Scheme. Il nome fu scelto per la passione dello stesso inventore verso i Monty Python e per la loro serie televisiva Monty Python's Flying Circus.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python is een programmeertaal die begin jaren 90 ontworpen en ontwikkeld werd door Guido van Rossum, destijds verbonden aan het Centrum voor Wiskunde en Informatica (daarvoor Mathematisch Centrum) in Amsterdam. De taal is mede gebaseerd op inzichten van professor Lambert Meertens, die de programmeertaal ABC ontworpen had, bedoeld als alternatief voor BASIC, maar dan met geavanceerde datastructuren. Inmiddels wordt de taal doorontwikkeld door een enthousiaste groep, tot juli 2018 geleid door Van Rossum. Deze groep wordt ondersteund door vrijwilligers op het internet. De Python Software Foundation leidt de ontwikkeling van Python. Python is vrije software.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python  uma linguagem de programao de alto nvel, interpretada de script, imperativa, orientada a objetos, funcional, de tipagem dinmica e forte. Foi lanada por Guido van Rossum em 1991. Atualmente, possui um modelo de desenvolvimento comunitrio, aberto e gerenciado pela organizao sem fins lucrativos Python Software Foundation. Apesar de vrias partes da linguagem possurem padres e especificaes formais, a linguagem, como um todo, no  formalmente especificada. O padro na pratica  a implementao CPython.

Jego skadnia cechuje si przejrzystoci i zwizoci. Python rozwijany jest jako projekt Open Source zarzdzany przez Python Software Foundation, ktra jest organizacj non-profit. Standardow implementacj jzyka jest CPython (napisany w C), ale istniej te inne, np. Jython (napisany w Javie), CLPython napisany w Common Lisp, IronPython (na platform .NET) i PyPy (napisany w Pythonie, zob. ).

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scala_(programming_language)
object: Scala is een object-functionele programmeer- en scripttaal voor algemene toepassingen. Het is statisch getypeerd, ontworpen om oplossingen bondig uit te drukken, op een type-veilige, elegante en lichtgewichte wijze. Het integreert de voordelen van objectgeorinteerde en functionele principes. Moderne software-constructies (closures, , staartrecursie etc.) kunnen opgezet worden met bijvoorbeeld genericiteit, hogere-ordefuncties, patroonvergelijking, meervoudige overerving, call-by-name-evaluatie etc. Scala draait op Java's virtual machine (JVM) en kan enkele tekortkomingen van Java wegnemen (bijvoorbeeld meervoudige-overerving van klassen).

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scala_(programming_language)
object: Scala (/skl/ SKAH-lah) is a strong statically typed general-purpose programming language which supports both object-oriented programming and functional programming. Designed to be concise, many of Scala's design decisions are aimed to address criticisms of Java. The name Scala is a portmanteau of scalable and language, signifying that it is designed to grow with the demands of its users.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scala_(programming_language)
object: Scala merupakan bahasa pemrograman umum (general purpose) yang mendukung pemrograman berorientasi objek dan pemrograman fungsional. Secara umum, tujuan dibuatnya Scala adalah untuk mengkritisi bahasa pemrograman Java.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scala_(programming_language)

Son nom vient de l'anglais Scalable language qui signifie  peu prs  langage adaptable  ou  langage qui peut tre mis  l'chelle . Il peut en effet tre vu comme un mtalangage. Il est prvu pour tre compil en bytecode Java (excutable sur la JVM), ou .NET. Seule la plateforme Java est supporte officiellement par l'EPFL.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mercury_(Modern_Visual_Basic_-_programming_language)
object: Mercury (known as Modern Visual Basic) is a programming language developed by RemObjects Software. Mercury is a revitalization of Microsoft Visual Basic.NET language which Microsoft ceased to enhance. RemObjects extends VB.Net underlying language and adds more features to it. Mercury is a commercial product and offers full integration into Microsoft's Visual Studio IDE on Windows, as well as RemObjects Elements IDE called Water on Windows or Fire on macOS. Mercury is the sixth language supported by the underlying Elements Compiler toolchain, next to C#, Swift, Java, Go and Oxygene.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/OpenQASM

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/OpenQASM
object: Open Quantum Assembly Language (OpenQASM; pronounced open kazm) is an intermediate representation for quantum instructions. The language was first described in a paper published in July 2017, and a reference source code implementation was released as part of IBM's Quantum Information Software Kit (Qiskit) for use with their IBM Quantum Experience cloud quantum computing platform. The language has similar qualities to traditional hardware description languages such as Verilog. OpenQASM defines its version at the head of a source file as a number, as in the declaration: OPENQASM 3;

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boo_(programming_language)
object: Boo je objektov orientovan, staticky typovan programovac jazyk. Jeho vvoj zaal v roce 2003 v souvislosti se vznikem Common Language Infrastructure. Sna se o vyuit podpory Unicode, monost tvorby vcejazynch aplikac (internationalization) a webovch aplikac. Jeho syntaxe byla inspirovna jazykem Python a zamuje se navc na roziitelnost jazyka a pekladae. Mezi zkladn rysy jazyka pat: Open source licence ve stylu MIT/BSD. Boo me bt pouit na platformch Microsoft .NET nebo Mono.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boo_(programming_language)
object: Boo is an object-oriented, statically typed, general-purpose programming language that seeks to make use of the Common Language Infrastructure's support for Unicode, internationalization, and web applications, while using a Python-inspired syntax and a special focus on language and compiler extensibility. Some features of note include type inference, generators, multimethods, optional duck typing, macros, true closures, currying, and first-class functions. Boo is free software released under the BSD 3-Clause license. It is compatible with the Microsoft .NET and Mono frameworks.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boo_(programming_language)
object: Boo est un langage de programmation objet, avec typage statique dont le dveloppement a commenc en 2003, cherchant  faire usage de la gestion de l'Unicode, de l'internationalisation et des applications web de la Common Language Infrastructure, tout en utilisant une syntaxe inspire de Python et en ayant une insistance sur l'extensibilit du langage et du compilateur. Parmi les caractristiques du langage figurent l'infrence de types, les gnrateurs, les multimthodes, le duck typing optionnel, les macro-dfinitions, les vraies fermetures, la curryfication et les fonctions de premire classe.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boo_(programming_language)
object: Boo  uma linguagem compilada e esttica e com uma sintaxe baseada no Python, combinando a clareza da sintaxe do Python com as garantias e desempenhos desejados em uma linguagem estaticamente tipada. Uma das coisas que mais chama ateno no Boo  o seu compilador extensvel. Em diversos estgios durante o processo de compilao, os desenvolvedores podem modificar o processo alterando a forma com que o compilador se comporta.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boomerang_(programming_language)
object: Boomerang is a programming language for writing lenseswell-behaved bidirectional transformations that operate on ad-hoc, textual data formats. Boomerang grew out of the Harmony generic data synchronizer, which grew out of the Unison file synchronization project.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boomerang_(programming_language)
object: Boomerang est un langage de programmation.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Join_Java
object: Join Java is a programming language based on the join-pattern that extends the standard Java programming language with the join semantics of the join-calculus. It was written at the University of South Australia within the Reconfigurable Computing Lab by Dr. Von Itzstein.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jolie_(programming_language)
object: Jolie je open source programovac jazyk zamen na orchestraci webovch slueb a tvorbu distribuovanch aplikac. Umouje jednodue a efektivn namodelovat business proces zahrnujc voln webovch slueb. Na rozdl od jazyku BPEL, kter je spjat s WSDL a SOAP zprvami, Jolie umouje i voln slueb, kter jsou zaloeny na jinm ne SOAP protokolu, napklad XML/RPC, JSON/RPC atd.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jolie_(programming_language)
object: Jolie (Java Orchestration Language Interpreter Engine) is an open-source programming language for developing distributed applications based on microservices. In the programming paradigm proposed with Jolie, each program is a service that can communicate with other programs by sending and receiving messages over a network. Jolie supports an abstraction layer that allows services to communicate using different mediums, ranging from TCP/IP sockets to local in-memory communications between processes.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_(programming_language)
object: Julia, en cincia de la computaci, s un llenguatge de programaci dinmic d'alt nivell adreat a l'anlisi numrica per tamb es pot considerar com un llenguatge de propsit general. Julia implementa un compilador sofisticat, execuci en parallel, precisi numrica i una biblioteca de funcions matemtiques extensa (lgebra lineal, generaci de nombres aleatoris, processament de senyal i de cadenes de carcters).

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_(programming_language)
object: Julia je dynamick programovac jazyk uren zejmna pro vdeck vpoty. Jeho vvoj zaal v roce 2009 a uveejnn pod svobodnou licenc byl roku 2012. Snadno umouje paraleln a distribuovan vpoty a doke pmo volat rutiny psan v C a Fortranu. Jdro jazyka Julia je implementovno v C a C++. Na vysokorovov jazyk vykazuje Julia mimodnou rychlost, asto srovnatelnou s programem psanm pmo v jazyce C. Zajmav tak je, e Julia je svm vlastnm makrojazykem a program je mono modifikovat pmo za bhu, co umouje snadn metaprogramovn.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_(programming_language)

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_(programming_language)
object: Julia ist eine hhere Programmiersprache, die vor allem fr numerisches und wissenschaftliches Rechnen entwickelt wurde und auch als Allzweck-Programmiersprache verwendet werden kann, bei gleichzeitiger Wahrung einer hohen Ausfhrungsgeschwindigkeit. Die Syntax erinnert stark an Matlab, wie auch an andere technische Programmiersprachen. Der Compiler wurde in C, C++ und Scheme geschrieben; die Standardbibliothek ist in Julia selbst geschrieben. Die Programmiersprache, deren Entwicklung 2009 begann, wurde im Februar 2012 als Open Source verffentlicht.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_(programming_language)
object: Julia es un lenguaje de programacin homoicnico, multiplataforma y multiparadigma de tipado dinmico de alto nivel y alto desempeo para la computacin genrica, tcnica y cientfica, con una sintaxis similar a la de otros entornos de computacin similares. El nombre del lenguaje Julia fue una ocurrencia de los creadores.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_(programming_language)
object: Julia is a high-level, dynamic programming language. Its features are well suited for numerical analysis and computational science. Distinctive aspects of Julia's design include a type system with parametric polymorphism in a dynamic programming language; with multiple dispatch as its core programming paradigm. Julia supports concurrent, (composable) parallel and distributed computing (with or without using MPI or the built-in corresponding to "OpenMP-style" threads), and direct calling of C and Fortran libraries without glue code. Julia uses a just-in-time (JIT) compiler that is referred to as "just-ahead-of-time" (JAOT) in the Julia community, as Julia compiles all code (by default) to machine code before running it.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_(programming_language)
object: Julia est un langage de programmation de haut niveau, performant et dynamique pour le calcul scientifique, avec une syntaxe familire aux utilisateurs d'autres environnements de dveloppement similaires (Matlab, R, Scilab, Python, etc.). Il fournit un compilateur sophistiqu, un systme de types dynamiques avec polymorphisme paramtr, une excution parallle distribue, des appels directs de fonctions C, Fortran et Python.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_(programming_language)
object: Julia,  un linguaggio di programmazione, multi-paradigma, open source pubblicato a partire dal 2012 (anche se le basi furono poste nel 2009) da un gruppo di programmatori impegnati professionalmente nel campo del calcolo numerico pensato con lo scopo di fornire uno strumento ad alte prestazioni dedicato in maniera particolare al mondo della programmazione scientifica. Scritto in C++ e Scheme questo linguaggio si basa su di un compilatore JIT (Just In Time) che si appoggia a sua volta sul noto framework LLVM. Fin dalle prime fasi dello sviluppo gli autori si sono impegnati nel fornire al linguaggio un adeguato supporto di librerie implementate tra l'altro in gran parte in Julia stesso ponendo nel contempo grande enfasi sulle prestazioni che dovevano essere comparabili con quelle ottenute i

Em 2020, um estudo com 20.000 pessoas feita pela empresa tchca JetBrains apontou que apenas 1% dos entrevistados usava Julia em seu ecossistema. No entanto, o nmero de usurios tem crescido de forma expressiva, assim como pacotes desenvolvidos em Julia, de tal forma que, entre janeiro de 2020 e janeiro de 2021, a linguagem saiu da posio 47 para a posio 23 no ranking do ndice TIOBE.

object: Little b is a domain-specific programming language, more specifically, a modeling language, designed to build modular mathematical models of biological systems. It was designed and authored by . Little b is being developed in the Virtual Cell Program at Harvard Medical School, headed by mathematician Jeremy Gunawardena. This language is based on Lisp and is meant to allow modular programming to model biological systems. It will allow more flexibility to facilitate rapid change that is required to accurately capture complex biological systems.

Estructuralmente, Perl est basado en un estilo de bloques como los del C o AWK, y fue ampliamente adoptado por su destreza en el procesado de texto y no tener ninguna de las limitaciones de los otros lenguajes de script.

object: Perl [pl] ist eine freie, plattformunabhngige und interpretierte Programmiersprache, die mehrere Paradigmen untersttzt. subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perl

"Perl" refers to Perl 5, but from 2000 to 2019 it also referred to its redesigned "sister language", Perl 6, before the latter's name was officially changed to Raku in October 2019. Perl is a highly expressive programming language: source code for a given algorithm can be short and highly compressible.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perl
object: Perl est un langage de programmation cr par Larry Wall en 1987 pour traiter facilement de l'information de type textuel. Ce langage, interprt, s'inspire des structures de contrle et d'impression du langage C, mais aussi de langages de scripts sed, awk et shell (sh). Il prend en charge les expressions rgulires dans sa syntaxe mme, permettant ainsi directement des actions sur l'aspect gnral de squences de texte.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perl
object: Perl adalah bahasa pemrograman untuk segala keperluan, dikembangkan pertama kali oleh Larry Wall di mesin Unix. Perl dirilis pertama kali pada tanggal 18 Desember 1987 ditandai dengan keluarnya Perl 1. Pada versi-versi selanjutnya, Perl tersedia pula untuk berbagai sistem operasi varian Unix (SunOS, Linux, BSD, HP-UX), juga tersedia untuk sistem operasi seperti DOS, Microsoft Windows, PowerPC, , , EBCDIC, dan . Dukungan terhadap pemrograman berbasis objek (object oriented programming/OOP) ditambahkan pada Perl 5, yang pertama kali dirilis pada tanggal 31 Juli 1993. Proyek pengembangan Perl 6 dimulai pada tahun 2000, dan masih berlangsung hingga kini tanpa tanggal yang jelas kapan mau dirilis. Ini dikatakan sendiri oleh Larry Wall dalam satu pidatonya yang dikenal dengan seri .

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perl

Originalmente, Perl foi desenvolvida por Larry Wall em 1987; desde ento, a linguagem passou por muitas atualizaes e revises at chegar  verso Perl 5 em 1994. Perl 6, desenvolvido a partir do Perl 5 em 2000, eventualmente evoluiu para uma linguagem distinta. Ambas as linguagens continuam a ser desenvolvidas independentemente por equipes diferentes.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Petit_Computer
object: Petit Computer is a software development application for the Nintendo DSi and later systems, developed by SmileBoom in Sapporo, Japan. The application is built around a custom dialect of BASIC known as SmileBASIC (not to be confused with the 3DS sequel with the same name). Users can write games and other software using the onscreen keyboard and run the applications from within Petit Computer. The platform supports text-based console applications, visual applications, and any combination of the two. Input is available via hardware buttons, touchscreen input, or the onscreen keyboard.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ring_(programming_language)
object: Ring est un langage de programmation dynamique. Il peut tre intgr dans les projets C/C++, tendues  l'aide de code C/C++ et/ou utilis comme une application autonome de la langue.Le langage est portable (Windows, Linux, Mac OS X, Android, etc.) et peut tre utilis pour crer des applications de console, GUI, Web, jeu et mobile.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ring_(programming_language)
object: Ring is a dynamically typed, general-purpose programming language. It can be embedded in C/C++ projects, extended using C/C++ code and/or used as a standalone language. The supported programming paradigms are imperative, procedural, object-oriented, functional, meta, declarative using nested structures, and natural programming. The language is portable (Windows, Linux, macOS, Android, WebAssembly, etc.) and can be used to create console, GUI, web, game and mobile applications.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/DIBOL
object: DIBOL or Digital's Business Oriented Language is a general-purpose, procedural, imperative programming language, designed for use in Management Information Systems (MIS) software development. It has a syntax similar to FORTRAN and BASIC, along with BCD arithmetic. It shares the COBOL program structure of separate data and procedure divisions. Unlike Fortran's numeric labels (for GOTO), DIBOL's were alphanumeric; the language supported a counterpart to computed goto.

Vala hat das Ziel, eine moderne Programmiersprache fr die Entwicklung mit dem Objektsystem GObject (das Fundament aller GTK+-/Gnome-Anwendungen) zu bieten, ohne die Notwendigkeit einer zustzlichen Laufzeitbibliothek (im Gegensatz zu Mono oder Java). Zudem ist die Binrschnittstelle kompatibel mit Applikationen und Bibliotheken, die in C geschrieben sind.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vala_(programming_language)
object: Vala es un lenguaje de programacin creado con el objetivo de acercar las caractersticas de los lenguajes modernos a C, sin requisitos adicionales de tiempo de ejecucin y con pocos costos, centrado en los objetos de la biblioteca GObject. Ha sido desarrollado por Jrg Billeter y Raffaele Sandrini. Actualmente es desarrollado y mantenido por Rico Tzschichholz. La sintaxis se inspira en C#, con leves modificaciones para adaptarse mejor al sistema de objetos de GObject.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vala_(programming_language)
object: Vala est un langage de programmation compil, dont l'objectif est de fournir les bnfices des langages de programmation modernes (comme la POO) aux dveloppeurs de la plateforme GNOME qui utilisent GLib et son systme GObject. Par exemple, les logiciels Shotwell, Geary, GNOME Contacts ou le greffon Arte+7 pour Totem sont crits en Vala.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vala_(programming_language)
object: Vala is an object-oriented programming language with a self-hosting compiler that generates C code and uses the GObject system. Vala is syntactically similar to C# and includes notable features such as anonymous functions, signals, properties, generics, assisted memory management, exception handling, type inference, and foreach statements. Its developers, Jrg Billeter and Raffaele Sandrini, wanted to bring these features to the plain C runtime with little overhead and no special runtime support by targeting the GObject object system. Rather than compiling directly to machine code or assembly language, it compiles to a lower-level intermediate language. It source-to-source compiles to C, which is then compiled with a C compiler for a given platform, such as GCC or Clang.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Visual_Basic_(classic)
object: The original Visual Basic (also referred to as Classic Visual Basic) is a third-generation event-driven programming language from Microsoft known for its Component Object Model (COM) programming model first released in 1991 and declared legacy during 2008. Microsoft intended Visual Basic to be relatively easy to learn and use. Visual Basic was derived from BASIC and enables the rapid application development (RAD) of graphical user interface (GUI) applications, access to databases using Data Access Objects, Remote Data Objects, or ActiveX Data Objects, and creation of ActiveX controls and objects.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Visual_FoxPro
object: Microsoft Visual FoxPro (VFP) ist eine 2007 abgekndigte RAD-Programmierumgebung von Microsoft fr datenzentrierte Anwendungen. Sie basiert auf einer objektorientierten Programmiersprache (deren prozedurale Basis eine stark erweiterte xBase-Sprache ist) und auf einem relationalen Datenbanksystem. Neben klassischen Desktop-Anwendungen auf Basis des integrierten Datenbanksystems werden auch server- und webbasierte Lsungen entwickelt. Microsoft sagte einen Produktsupport fr diese Version bis zum Januar 2015 zu. Eine Weiterentwicklung wurde durch Microsoft ausgeschlossen.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Visual_FoxPro
object: FoxPro et Visual FoxPro (VFP) sont des outils ayant t commercialiss par puis par Microsoft de 1989  son abandon en 2007. Visual FoxPro comprend un langage de programmation, un moteur de base de donnes relationnelles et un environnement de dveloppement intgr (IDE). Il est utilis pour grer les donnes, organiser des tables d'informations par des requtes, en crant une gestion intgre de base de donnes de type relationnelles (DBMS). La dernire version permet de construire des solutions compltes, depuis les formulaires d'acquisitions jusquaux sorties de rapports complexes dans un environnement client/serveur, bureautique ou pour le web. En mars 2007, Microsoft annonce l'abandon de ce logiciel, qui sera toutefois support jusqu'en janvier 2015 pour la dernire version.

object: Visual FoxPro (VFP)  un linguaggio di programmazione che integra la programmazione di tipo procedurale e quella orientata agli oggetti.  pubblicato da Microsoft per Windows.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Visual_FoxPro
object: Visual FoxPro is een softwarepakket van Microsoft voor het creren en onderhouden van 32-bit database-applicaties en -componenten. Visual FoxPro is een objectgeorinteerde datacentrische programmeertaal. Het bevat een programmeertaal, een databaseengine en een Integrated Development Environment (IDE). Visual FoxPro heeft een systeem voor achterwaartse compatibiliteit, wat inhoudt dat verouderde code redelijk eenvoudig kan worden aangepast en verbeterd. Visual FoxPro is ook een Rapid Application Development (RAD)-tool, wat betekent dat het gericht is op het op een snelle manier software ontwikkelen.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Visual_FoxPro
object: Visual FoxPro, VFP  system zarzdzania baz danych, obiektowy i proceduralny dynamiczny jzyk programowania z wbudowanym wasnym relacyjnym silnikiem obsugi bazy danych oraz zintegrowane rodowisko programowania z Microsoftu. FoxPro jest jednym z jzykw z rodziny xBase z wbudowan obsug jzyka SQL. Visual FoxPro ma moliwo wsppracy z serwerami baz danych typu SQL, oraz rnymi rdami danych poprzez interfejsy OLE DB, ODBC, ADO oraz XML. Technologie wywodzce si z FoxPro s wykorzystywane przez Microsoft m.in. w SQL Server, Access oraz rnych czciach Visual Studio i .NET Framework.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Visual_FoxPro
object: Visual FoxPro is a Microsoft data-centric procedural programming language with object-oriented programming (OOP) features. It was derived from FoxPro (originally known as FoxBASE) which was developed by Fox Software beginning in 1984. Fox Technologies merged with Microsoft in 1992, after which the software acquired further features and the prefix "Visual". FoxPro 2.6 worked on Mac OS, DOS, Windows, and Unix. Version 9.0, released in December 2004 and updated in October 2007 with the SP2 patch, was the final version of the product.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deductive_language
object: A deductive language is a computer programming language in which the program is a collection of predicates ('facts') and rules that connect them. Such a language is used to create knowledge based systems or expert systems which can deduce answers to problem sets by applying the rules to the facts they have been given.An example of a deductive language is Prolog, or its database-query cousin, Datalog.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/EXAPT
object: EXAPT ("EXtended Subset of APT") ist eine fertigungstechnisch orientierte Programmiersprache zur Erzeugung von NC-Programmen, um Steuerungsinformationen fr Werkzeugmaschinen zu generieren, und ermglicht die Bercksichtigung fertigungstechnischer Belange verschiedener Bearbeitungsverfahren. EXAPT ist nach industriellen Anforderungen historisch gewachsen. Es wurden im Laufe der Jahre diverse Software-Lsungen fr die Fertigungsindustrie geschaffen, die heute ein breites, skalierbares Leistungsspektrum mit zukunftsorientierten Produkten und Dienstleistungen bilden.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/EXAPT
object: EXAPT ("EXtended Subset of APT") is a production oriented programming language to generate NC programs with control information for machining tools and enables to consider production-related issues of various machining processes. EXAPT has developed historically regarding industrial requirements. Through the years software solutions for the manufacturing industry were created which today form a broad scalable portfolio with future-oriented products and services.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/E_(programming_language)
object: E ist eine objektorientierte Programmiersprache fr sicheres verteiltes Rechnen, die 1997 von Mark S. Miller, Dan Bornstein, Douglas Crockford, Chip Morningstar und anderen bei der Firma entwickelt wurde. E stammt hauptschlich von den nebenlufigen Sprachen Joule und Original-E ab, einer Reihe von Erweiterungen fr Java zur sicheren verteilten Programmierung. E kombiniert nachrichtenbasierte Berechnungen mit einer Java-hnlichen Syntax. Ein Nebenlufigkeitsmodell, das auf Ereignisschleifen und Promises basiert, stellt sicher, dass es nie zu einem Deadlock kommen kann.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/E_(programming_language)
object: E is an object-oriented programming language for secure distributed computing, created by Mark S. Miller, Dan Bornstein, Douglas Crockford, Chip Morningstar and others at Electric Communities in 1997. E is mainly descended from the concurrent language Joule and from Original-E, a set of extensions to Java for secure distributed programming. E combines message-based computation with Java-like syntax. A concurrency model based on event loops and promises ensures that deadlock can never occur.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/E_(programming_language)
object: E  uma linguagem de programao orientada a objetos para segurana de computao distribuda, criada por , e outros da comunidade de eletricistas em 1997. E  descendente principalmente de uma linguagem concorrente, o Joule e do , um conjunto de extenses da linguagem Java para computao distribuda. A linguagem E combina programao baseada em troca de mensagens com a sintaxe do Java.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/E_(programming_language)
object: E  obiektowo zorientowany jzyk programowania (zob. programowanie obiektowe) przeznaczony dla bezpiecznych oblicze rozproszonych, stworzony przez Marka S. Millera i innych w Electric Communities w roku 1997. E wywodzi si gwnie ze wspbienego i oryginalnego E, czyli rozszerzenia jzyka Java do bezpiecznych oblicze rozproszonych. E czy przetwarzanie oparte na komunikatach ze skadni jzyka Java. Model wspbienoci stosowany w E zapewnia, e nigdy nie nastpi zakleszczenie.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/E_(programming_language)
object: E r ett programsprk. Det r ett objektorienterat skriptsprk avsett fr skra distribuerade tillmpningar. E skapades 1997 och tog sin utgngspunkt i sprket Joule och Original-E, ett antal tillgg till Java fr sker distribuerad programmering.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/TREE-META
object: TREE-META (nebo Tree Meta, TREEMETA) Translator Writing System je genertor peklada pro bezkontextov jazyky vytvoen v 60. letech 20. stolet. Pkazy metajazyka pro syntaktickou analzu se podobaj rozen BackusovNaurov form s vloenmi direktivami pro vytven stromu. Pravidla pro tak zvan unparsing obsahuj mnostv konstrukt pro prci se stromovmi strukturami a pro generovn kdu.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/TREE-META
object: The TREE-META (or Tree Meta, TREEMETA) Translator Writing System is a compiler-compiler system for context-free languages originally developed in the 1960s. Parsing statements of the metalanguage resemble augmented BackusNaur form with embedded tree-building directives. Unparsing rules include extensive tree-scanning and code-generation constructs.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concordion
object:
Concordion is a specification by example framework originally developed by David Peterson, and now maintained by a team of contributors, led by Nigel Charman. Inspired by the Fit Framework, David states the following aims were behind Concordion:

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNOBOL
object: SNOBOL 4 (String Oriented symbolic Language number 4) ist die vierte und letzte Ausprgung einer Reihe von Programmiersprachen mit dem Zweck der Manipulation von Zeichenketten. Diese Sprachen wurden zwischen 1962 und 1967 in den Bell Laboratories von AT&T durch David J. Farber, Ralph E. Griswold und Ivan P. Polonsky entwickelt. Die Sprache SNOBOL 4 untersttzt eine Reihe von eingebauten Datentypen wie Integer- und Gleitkommazahlen, Zeichenketten, Mustern, Feldern und Tabellen. Darber hinaus gestattet sie dem Programmierer die Definition von zustzlichen Datentypen und neuen Funktionen.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNOBOL
object: SNOBOL ("StriNg Oriented and symBOlic Language") is a series of programming languages developed between 1962 and 1967 at AT&T Bell Laboratories by David J. Farber, Ralph E. Griswold and Ivan P. Polonsky, culminating in SNOBOL4. It was one of a number of text-string-oriented languages developed during the 1950s and 1960s; others included COMIT and TRAC. SNOBOL4 was quite widely taught in larger US universities in the late 1960s and early 1970s and was widely used in the 1970s and 1980s as a text manipulation language in the humanities.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNOBOL
object: SNOBOL (abrviation de StriNg Oriented symBOlic Language) est un langage de programmation bas sur le traitement des chanes de caractres. Il a t dfini entre 1960 et 1962 dans les Laboratoires Bell. Il est rest confidentiel jusqu' sa version 4 (SNOBOL4), qui a connu la clbrit grce  son algorithme de filtrage par motif trs puissant ; par contre sa syntaxe tait trs lie  la technologie des cartes perfores, et un programme en SNOBOL tait illisible une fois crit. Il a fortement influenc Unix  sa naissance, et ses descendants sont sed, awk et donc Perl.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNOBOL
object: SNOBOL (StriNg Oriented and symBOlic Language)  il nome generico di un linguaggio di programmazione per calcolatore sviluppato tra il 1962 e il 1967 da , e presso i Laboratori AT&T Bell. L'ultima versione del linguaggio ha preso il nome di SNOBOL4. SNOBOL  stato uno di una serie di linguaggi orientati alle stringhe sviluppato tra gli anni cinquanta e i sessanta (tra gli altri, e ). Uno dei progettisti di SNOBOL, Ralph Griswold, ne ide due successori, chiamati SL5 e Icon, che combinavano il meccanismo di pattern matching di SNOBOL4 con una strutturazione pi standard stile ALGOL.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/General-purpose_programming_language
object: Eine Allzweck-Programmiersprache (englisch General-purpose programming language, kurz GPL, auch Mehrzweck- oder Universalsprache) ist eine Programmiersprache, die fr viele Anwendungsflle/Problemstellungen einsetzbar ist. Allzweck-Programmiersprachen sind Turing-vollstndig, das heit, dass sie theoretisch jedes berechenbare Problem lsen knnen. Allzweck-Programmiersprachen stehen in Gegensatz zu den domnenspezifischen Sprachen (DSLs), die nur fr spezielle Anwendungsflle geeignet sind.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/General-purpose_programming_language
object: In computer software, a general-purpose programming language (GPL) is a programming language designed to be used for building software in a wide variety of application domains, across a multitude of hardware configurations and operating systems. In theory, a GPL program can run equivalently on a single processor or on a network. The opposite of a general-purpose programming language is a domain-specific programming language, which is designed to be used within a specific area, for example, querying databases. For example, SQL was designed for querying databases.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clascal
object: Clascal is a discontinued object-oriented programming language developed in 1983 by the Personal Office Systems (POS) division (later renamed The Lisa Division, then later The 32-Bit Systems Division) of Apple Computer. Clascal was used to program applications for the Lisa Office System, the operating environment of the Lisa. According to Larry Tesler, this was developed as a replacement for their version of Smalltalk that was too slow. Ultimately Object Pascal evolved into the language of Borland Delphi.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caml
object: Caml (originally an acronym for Categorical Abstract Machine Language) is a multi-paradigm, general-purpose programming language which is a dialect of the ML programming language family. Caml was developed in France at INRIA and ENS. Caml is statically typed, strictly evaluated, and uses automatic memory management. OCaml, the main descendant of Caml, adds many features to the language, including an object layer.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caml
object: Caml (Originalmente un acrnimo para Categorical Abstract Machine Language, en espaol Lenguaje Mquina Abstracto Categrico) es un dialecto de la familia del lenguaje ML, desarrollado en INRIA y anteriormente en la Escuela Normal Superior de Pars. Como muchos descendientes de ML, Caml es un lenguaje de tipado esttico, evaluacin estricta, y utiliza administracin de memoria automtica. La primera implementacin de Caml en Lisp fue apodada "CAML pesado" debido a los requisitos de memoria y CPU relativos a su sucesor "Caml Light", aquello fue implementado en C por Xavier Leroy y Damien Doligez.Adems de una reescritura completa, "CAML Special Light" aadi un potente sistema de mdulos al ncleo del lenguaje. Actualmente, la implementacin principal de Caml es , el cual aade muchas caractersticas nuevas al lenguaje, entre ellas una capa de objeto.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caml
object: Caml (prononc camel, signifie Categorical Abstract Machine Language) est un langage de programmation gnraliste conu pour la scurit et la fiabilit des programmes. Il se prte  des styles de programmation fonctionnelle, imprative et oriente objet. C'est de plus un langage fortement typ. Le style fonctionnel rapproche le langage Caml de lcriture mathmatique, notamment grce  la rcursivit et au filtrage par motif (pattern matching). Ce dernier, particularit de la famille ML, offre une syntaxe au cas par cas claire et lisible, et est aussi utilis dans le rattrapage des exceptions, en particulier pour la gestion des erreurs. Le typage fort rend lusage sr mais moins souple pour le programmeur. Enfin, Caml pratique linfrence de types pour dterminer automatiquement le type des variables et expressions et permet la gnricit. Descendant du langage ML, le Caml est dvelopp depuis 1985 par les quipes Formel puis Cristal de l'Inria et l'a notamment t pendant cinq ans par le professeur Guy Cousineau (universit Paris Diderot). La variante active de Caml est OCaml. Par rapport  l'ancienne variante Caml Light, aujourd'hui obsolte, elle ajoute de nombreuses fonctionnalits, comme un systme de modules beaucoup plus pouss et le support de la programmation oriente objet (reposant sur le duck typing) dont elle tire son nom.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caml
object: CAML (Categorical Abstract Machine Language)  una versione del linguaggio di programmazione ML sviluppata in Francia presso l'INRIA e l'cole Normale Suprieure (ENS). La sua prima implementazione, in Lisp,  stata soprannominata Heavy CAML per la richiesta di ingenti risorse computazionali in confronto al suo successore CAML Light, implementato in C da Xavier Leroy and Damien Doligez. Oltre alla completa riscrittura, CAML Light aggiunge al precedente nucleo del linguaggio un potente sistema di modularizzazione. Dal 1995,  stato aggiunto anche il trattamento degli oggetti e da allora il nome del linguaggio  mutato in OCaml.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caml
object: Caml, acrnimo de "Categorical Abstract MetaLanguage",  um dialeto da famlia de linguagens de programao do ML, desenvolvida pelo INRIA e pela cole Normale Suprieure. Como todos os descendentes do ML, Caml  uma linguagem de tipagem esttica, de avaliao estrita (strict evaluation) e usa gerenciamento automtico de memria. A primeira implementao Caml, feita em Lisp, foi apelidada de "Heavy CAML" (CAML pesado) por causa dos requisitos de CPU e memria excessivos se comparados com seu sucessor, o Caml light (Caml leve), que foi implementado em linguagem C por e . Alm de ser completamente reescrito, o CAML special Light acrescentou um poderoso sistema de mdulos na base da linguagem. Atualmente a principal implementao do Caml  o Objective Caml, que acrescenta vrias novas funcionalidades  linguagem, incluindo uma camada de orientao a objetos.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Behavioral_Description_Language
object: Behavioral Description Language (BDL) is a programming language based on ANSI C with extensions for hardware description, developed to describe hardware at levels ranging from the algorithm level to the functional level. Although the term Behavioral Description Language is a generic term and can refer to multiple high-level description languages, NEC Corporation has developed a C-subset called BDL for High-Level Synthesis. This C-subset includes its own data types (called var-class), special constants for hardware design e.g. high impedance, timing descriptors and control statements. As BDL is meant for Hardware synthesis, the complete ANSI-C syntax is not supported. The principal unsupported operations are: (i) Floating point data types (ii) Sizeof operator (iii) unions and (iv) Recursive functions. BDL is sometimes also known as Cyber C because it is synthesized using NEC's High-Level Synthesis tool called CyberWorkBench [1].

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing s una aplicaci de codi obert amb un llenguatge per a la programaci d'imatges, animaci, i so. El processing s un projecte de codi lliure iniciat per i ( U / ), i s desenvolupat per artistes i dissenyadors com a alternativa a eines de programari patentades en el mateix camp, com Macromedia Flash o . La seva sintaxi, basada en Java, est dissenyada per a programadors no gaire experimentats, s senzilla i molt semblant a l' de Flash (que est basat en JavaScript). s utilitzat per estudiants, artistes, dissenyadors, arquitectes, investigadors i aficionats. S'ha utilitzat per a ensenyar fonaments de programaci dins d'un context visual i com a eina de producci professional per a projectes artstics, arquitectnics o de disseny. Processing est disponible per a Linux, Mac OS X, i Windows.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing ist eine objektorientierte, stark typisierte Programmiersprache mit zugehriger integrierter Entwicklungsumgebung. Die Programmiersprache ist auf die Einsatzbereiche Grafik, Simulation und Animation spezialisiert. Processing wird in einem quelloffenen Projekt entwickelt, das am Massachusetts Institute of Technology von Ben Fry (Broad Institute) und Casey Reas (UCLA Design|Media Arts) initiiert wurde. Processing hat den Charakter einer stark vereinfachten Version der Programmiersprache Java, ermglicht Interaktionen und visuelle Elemente zu programmieren und richtet sich vorwiegend an Gestalter, Knstler und Programmieranfnger. Die Klassenbibliotheken der Programmiersprache zielen vor allem auf das Einsatzgebiet von Processing ab und bercksichtigen die Themen Video, Grafik, Grafikformate, Sound, Animation, Typographie, 3D, Simulation, Datenzugriff und -transfer, sowie Netzwerkprotokolle. Im Jahr 2005 wurde Processing mit einer Goldenen Nica des Prix Ars Electronica in der Kategorie Net Vision/Net Excellence ausgezeichnet.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing (autrefois typographi Proce55ing) est un environnement de dveloppement libre (sous licence GNU GPL), cr par et , deux artistes amricains. Processing est le prolongement  multimdia  de , l'environnement de programmation graphique dvelopp par John Maeda au Media Lab du Massachusetts Institute of Technology. Processing est tout particulirement adapt  la cration plastique et graphique interactive et au graphisme de donnes, mais sa simplicit d'utilisation en fait aussi un bon support pour l'apprentissage de la logique de la programmation pour les non-programmeurs. Le logiciel fonctionne sur Macintosh, Windows, Linux, BSD et Android. Il est bas sur la plate-forme Java  il permet d'ailleurs de programmer directement en langage Java. Plusieurs langages peuvent dsormais tre utiliss au sein de l'environnement Processing : Javascript, avec Processing.js, et p5.js, excutables dans un environnement HTML 5 ou via node.js., REPL, Python ou encore R. Les programmes raliss avec Processing en mode Java peuvent tre exports sous forme d'applications indpendantes pour Windows, Linux ou Mac OS X (en ralit n'importe quelle machine disposant d'une machine virtuelle Java).

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing es un lenguaje de programacin y entorno de desarrollo integrado de cdigo abierto basado en Java, de fcil utilizacin, y que sirve como medio para la enseanza y produccin de proyectos multimedia e interactivos de diseo digital. Fue iniciado por y , ambos miembros de Aesthetics and Computation Group del MIT Media Lab dirigido por John Maeda. Uno de los objetivos declarados de Processing es el de actuar como herramienta para que artistas, diseadores visuales y miembros de otras comunidades ajenos al lenguaje de la programacin, aprendieran las bases de la misma a travs de una muestra grfica instantnea y visual de la informacin. El lenguaje de Processing se basa en , aunque hace uso de elementos de programacin sencillos, por lo que no se requieren conocimientos profundos en Java . Processing utiliza una sintaxis simplificada y un modelo de programacin de grficos.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing is a free graphical library and integrated development environment (IDE) built for the electronic arts, new media art, and visual design communities with the purpose of teaching non-programmers the fundamentals of computer programming in a visual context. Processing uses the Java language, with additional simplifications such as additional classes and aliased mathematical functions and operations. It also provides a graphical user interface for simplifying the compilation and execution stage. The Processing language and IDE have been the precursor to other projects including Arduino and Wiring.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing  un linguaggio di programmazione che consente di sviluppare applicazioni di vario tipo, come videogiochi, animazioni, contenuti interattivi e opere d'arte generativa. Eredita tutta la sintassi, i comandi e il paradigma di programmazione orientata agli oggetti dal linguaggio Java ma in pi mette a disposizione numerose funzioni ad alto livello per gestire in modo facile gli aspetti grafici e multimediali.  distribuito nei termini della licenza libera GNU General Public License (GPL) ed  compatibile con i sistemi operativi Linux, macOS e Microsoft Windows. Processing pu interagire con la scheda hardware Arduino.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing is opensourcesoftware ontwikkeld door en. Het biedt de mogelijkheid aan kunstenaars, ontwerpers, studenten en hobbyisten om de fundamenten van het programmeren binnen een visuele context te leren. Processing is een uitbreiding van Java, waardoor bestaande Java-structuren, vaak met vereenvoudigde syntaxis, worden ondersteund. Programma's worden gexporteerd naar Java-applets die als stand-alone applicatie of binnen een webpagina kunnen worden getoond. De software biedt een eenvoudige IDE voor het organiseren van de projecten. Het programma is gemaakt om als opensource-alternatief te dienen voor vergelijkbare commercile softwarepakketten, zoals Vuo. Het is beschikbaar voor Windows, Mac OS X en Linux. Processing wordt onder andere gebruikt voor Arduino-microcontrollers.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing  uma linguagem de programao de cdigo aberto e ambiente de desenvolvimento integrado (IDE), construdo para as artes eletrnicas e comunidades de projetos visuais com o objetivo de ensinar noes bsicas de programao de computador em um contexto visual e para servir como base para cadernos eletrnicos. O projeto foi iniciado em 2001 por e , ambos ex-membros do Grupo de Computao do MIT Media Lab. Um dos objetivos do Processing  atuar como uma ferramenta para no-programadores iniciados com a programao, atravs da satisfao imediata com um retorno visual. A linguagem tem por base as capacidades grficas da linguagem de programao Java, simplificando caractersticas e criar alguns novos.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Processing
object: Processing  jzyk programowania oraz zintegrowane rodowisko programistyczne (IDE) stworzone na potrzeby sztuki elektronicznej (wizualnej, interaktywnej, dwikowej) oraz projektowania graficznego. Autorami projektu s byli studenci i pracownicy Aesthetics and Computation Group (ACG) dziaajcym w w amerykaskim MIT, i . Processing oparty jest w duej mierze na wczeniejszym projekcie edukacyjnym szefa ACG,  . W obu przypadkach jednym z zaoe projektu byo przygotowanie rodowiska programistycznego, ktre pomoe w nauce programowania osb niezwizanych z programowaniem. Cel ten osignity jest przez byskawiczne efekty wizualne, jakie oferuje programowanie w jzyku Processing oraz przez uproszczenie skomplikowanych i pracochonnych konstrukcji programowania graficznego w jzyku Java, w ktrym Processing jest zaimplementowany.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/PureBasic
object: PureBasic es un compilador de un dialecto del lenguaje de programacin BASIC. Incluye entorno de programacin, con un amplio repertorio de instrucciones y libreras. Una de sus principales caractersticas frente a otros es la de generar ejecutables muy rpidos y pequeos. Puede compilar programas para Microsoft Windows, Linux, Mac OS X y AmigaOS a partir del mismo cdigo fuente. Ha sido creado por la empresa francesa Fantaisie Software. Permite usar directamente las funciones de la API del sistema operativo, como cualquier otra funcin. As mismo, es posible aadir directamente instrucciones en ensamblador (ASM) que operen con las variables utilizadas por el cdigo BASIC. As, el programador puede optimizar partes del cdigo en las cuales la velocidad de proceso es fundamental. Gracias a su versatilidad y a su facilidad de aprendizaje y uso, es muy sencillo crear en poco tiempo tanto juegos como aplicaciones, para lo cual incluye un diseador visual de ventanas y controles. He aqu un ejemplo de un programa sencillo en PureBasic: OpenConsole Print("Hola, mundo!") Delay(3000) CloseConsole El mismo ejemplo con uso de variables: Texto.s = "Hola, mundo!" ;El texto es guardado en una variable de texto(ver el .s al ;final de la variable) OpenConsole ;Abre la consola Print(Texto.s) ;Imprime el mensaje en pantalla Delay(3000) ;Hace una pausa de 3000 ms CloseConsole ;Cierra la consola PureBasic, se puede tambin comparar con otros lenguajes tales como Visual Basic. He aqu un ejemplo sobre como mostrar el mismo mensaje en una caja de mensaje...: En Visual Basic: MsgBox "HOLA", vbOKOnly, "Hola, Mundo" En PureBasic: MessageRequester("HOLA", "Hola, mundo",#PB_MessageRequester_Ok)

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/PureBasic
object: PureBasic is a commercially distributed procedural computer programming language and integrated development environment based on BASIC and developed by for Windows, Linux, and macOS. An Amiga version is available, although it has been discontinued and some parts of it are released as open-source. The first public release of PureBasic for Windows was on 17 December 2000. It has been continually updated ever since. PureBasic has a "lifetime license model". As cited on the website, the first PureBasic user (who registered in 1998) still has free access to new updates and this is not going to change. PureBasic compiles directly to IA-32, x86-64, PowerPC or 680x0 instruction sets, generating small standalone executables and DLLs which need no runtime libraries beyond the standard system libraries. Programs developed without using the platform-specific application programming interfaces (APIs) can be built easily from the same source file with little or no modification. PureBasic supports inline assembly, allowing the developer to include FASM assembler commands within PureBasic source code, while using the variables declared in PureBasic source code, enabling experienced programmers to improve the speed of speed-critical sections of code. PureBasic supports and has integrated the OGRE 3D Environment. Other 3D environments such as the Irrlicht Engine are unofficially supported.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/PureBasic
object:
PureBasic est un langage de programmation de type BASIC compil. Plusieurs points le caractrisent : 
* Simplicit : la syntaxe BASIC est simple  apprendre. 
* Rapidit : les applications produites sont optimises (taille rduite) et rapides. 
* Portabilit : le code source est portable d'un systme d'exploitation  l'autre. Il existe une version de PureBasic pour Linux, Windows, AmigaOS, et Mac OS. 
* Sans dpendances logicielles : le langage ainsi que les applications ne ncessitent pas d'installation obligatoire, il est donc ais de le transporter sur une cl USB, et d'excuter les applications sous forme d'applications portables. 
* Cration de fichiers DLL : la cration de DLL standard (Non ActiveX, utilisable dans n'importe quel autre langage) est aussi aise que la cration d'EXE. 
* Le prix : les mises  niveau sont gratuites  vie. PureBasic possde un jeu de commandes tendues (plus de 1 400 commandes internes) auxquelles s'ajoute un accs simplifi  une grande partie de l'API du systme d'exploitation. Le programmeur peut appeler les commandes de l'API de Windows, de Linux ou Mac OS directement comme s'il s'agissait des commandes internes  PureBasic, sans avoir  les dclarer au pralable (ainsi que les constantes). Rien de mieux qu'un exemple pratique pour illustrer ceci. Comparons un programme simple en Visual Basic avec son quivalent en PureBasic : comment obtenir le chemin du rpertoire Windows. Visual Basic:Private Declare Function GetWindowsDirectory Lib "kernel32" Alias "GetWindowsDirectoryA" _(ByVal lpBuffer As String, ByVal nSize As Long) As LongConst MAX_PATH = 260strWindowsDirectory$ = Space$(MAX_PATH)lngReturn& = GetWindowsDirectory(strWindowsDirectory$, MAX_PATH)PureBasic:strWindowsDirectory$ = Space(#MAX_PATH)lngReturn = GetWindowsDirectory_(strWindowsDirectory$, #MAX_PATH)

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/PureBasic
object: PureBasic, ontwikkeld door Frdric Laboureur (Fantaisie Software, Frankrijk), is een commercile compiler voor Windows, Linux, AmigaOS en Mac OS. De programma's zijn klein en snel, de syntaxis een mix tussen BASIC en C. Naast de vele krachtig geoptimaliseerde bibliotheken (GUI-gadgets, beeld, geluid, netwerk, database, compressie, cryptografie, ....) kan men rechtstreeks WinAPI aanspreken en Assembler-code gebruiken (Inline-Assembler). Bovendien is het mogelijk om een bibliotheek te schrijven. Verder biedt PureBasic sinds versie 3.5 een basale 3D-engine (OGRE 3D), waarmee het mogelijk is snel en eenvoudig kleine 3-D toepassingen te programmeren. Een essentieel voordeel vergeleken met andere programmeertalen is het bijzondere feit dat de taal doorlopend ontwikkeld wordt, steeds krachtiger wordt en dat nieuwe instructies de taal verder optimaliseren. De aanschaf van PureBasic houdt automatisch in dat alle toekomstige updates gratis zijn in de vorm van downloads. Verdere kosten bij het verkopen van door u ontwikkelde programma's zijn er niet, geschreven programma's kunnen licentie-vrij verhandeld worden zonder rekening te hoeven houden met beperkingen van de kant van de fabrikant. Op 4 november 2007 is versie 4.10 uitgebracht voor 3 platforms tegelijk: Windows, Linux en Mac OS. Het is de bedoeling dat het gelijktijdig uitbrengen van releases voor deze 3 platforms voortaan standaard wordt. AmigaOS wordt echter niet meer ondersteund. OpenConsole ; opent de console Print("Hello world!") ; weergave van tekst in de console Delay(3000) ; uitvoering programma wordt 3000 milliseconden gestopt CloseConsole ; console weer sluiten ; PureBasic code (4.10) dat een klein simpel venstertje opent (zonder knoppen); in gecompileerde vorm (.exe) is de grootte slechts 10,5 KB (10.752 bytes) If OpenWindow(1, 300, 300, 150, 50, "Voorbeeld 1", #PB_Window_SystemMenu) Repeat Variabele = WaitWindowEvent Select Variabele Case #PB_Event_CloseWindow End Case #PB_Event_Gadget EndSelect ForEverEndIf ; PureBasic code kan ook heel wat korter:If OpenWindow(2, 300, 300, 150, 50, "Voorbeeld 2", #PB_Window_SystemMenu) While WaitWindowEvent <> #PB_Event_CloseWindow : WendEndIf

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python s un llenguatge de programaci d'alt nivell i propsit general molt utilitzat. Va ser creat per Guido van Rossum l'any 1991. La seva filosofia de disseny busca llegibilitat en el codi i la seva sintaxi permet als programadors expressar conceptes en menys lnies de codi del que seria possible en llenguatges com C. Tamb proveeix estructures per permetre programes ms entenedors tant a petita com a gran escala. Python suporta diversos paradigmes de programaci, incloent-hi programaci orientada a objectes (POO), imperativa i tamb funcional o . Presenta un sistema dinmic i una gesti de la memria automtica i t una gran i exhaustiva biblioteca estndard. Com altres llenguatges de programaci dinmics, Python s usat sovint com un llenguatge script, per tamb es fa servir en una mplia gamma de contextos no-script. Utilitzant eines desenvolupades per tercers com , o , el codi Python pot ser redut a programes executables independents. Existeixen intrprets de Python per molts sistemes operatius diferents. CPython, la implementaci de referncia de Python, s programari lliure i de codi obert i t un model de desenvolupament basat en la comunitat, de la mateixa manera que la major part de les altres implementacions. s controlat per l'organitzaci sense nim de lucre Python Software Foundation, creada el 6 mar 2001. La missi de la fundaci s fomentar el desenvolupament de la comunitat Python. s responsable de diversos processos dins de la comunitat, com el desenvolupament de Python, l'administraci dels drets intellectuals i d'obtenir fons.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python (anglick vslovnost [pain]) je vysokorovov programovac jazyk, kter v roce 1991 navrhl Guido van Rossum. Nabz dynamickou kontrolu datovch typ a podporuje rzn programovac paradigmata, vetn objektov orientovanho, imperativnho, procedurlnho nebo funkcionlnho. V roce 2018 vzrostla jeho popularita a zaadil se mezi nejoblbenj jazyky. V ad rznch ebk dosahuje jedno z prvnch tech mst, vjimkou nebvaj prvn msta. Python je vyvjen jako open source projekt, kter zdarma nabz instalan balky pro vtinu bnch platforem (Unix, MS Windows, macOS, Android); ve vtin distribuc systmu GNU/Linux je Python soust zkladn instalace. Mimo jin je v nm implementovn aplikan server Zope, instaltor a vtina konfiguranch nstroj Linuxov distribuce firmy Red Hat. Python byl pojmenovn podle komediln skupiny Monty Python, kte pomoc svch ske ovlivnili internetovou subkulturu napklad slovem spam. Logo Pythonu je zase pejato z vznamu slova python, kter je v anglitin pouvno jako oznaen pro krajtu.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python ([pan], [pan], auf Deutsch auch [pytn]) ist eine universelle, blicherweise interpretierte, hhere Programmiersprache. Sie hat den Anspruch, einen gut lesbaren, knappen Programmierstil zu frdern. So werden beispielsweise Blcke nicht durch geschweifte Klammern, sondern durch Einrckungen strukturiert. Python untersttzt mehrere Programmierparadigmen, z. B. die objektorientierte, die aspektorientierte und die funktionale Programmierung. Ferner bietet es eine dynamische Typisierung. Wie viele dynamische Sprachen wird Python oft als Skriptsprache genutzt. Die Sprache weist ein offenes, gemeinschaftsbasiertes Entwicklungsmodell auf, das durch die gemeinntzige Python Software Foundation gesttzt wird, die die Definition der Sprache in der Referenzumsetzung CPython pflegt.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python es un lenguaje de alto nivel de programacin interpretado cuya filosofa hace hincapi en la legibilidad de su cdigo, se utiliza para desarrollar aplicaciones de todo tipo, ejemplos: Instagram, Netflix, Spotify, Panda3D, entre otros. Se trata de un lenguaje de programacin multiparadigma, ya que soporta parcialmente la orientacin a objetos, programacin imperativa y, en menor medida[cul?], programacin funcional. Es un lenguaje interpretado, dinmico y multiplataforma. Administrado por Python Software Foundation, posee una licencia de cdigo abierto, denominada Python Software Foundation License. Python se clasifica constantemente como uno de los lenguajes de programacin ms populares.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python adalah bahasa pemrograman yang , tingkat tinggi. Dibuat oleh Guido van Rossum dan pertama kali dirilis pada tahun 1991, filosofi desain Python menekankan keterbacaan kode dengan penggunaan . nya dan pendekatan berorientasi objek bertujuan untuk membantu pemrogram menulis kode yang jelas dan logis untuk proyek skala kecil dan besar. Python diketik secara dinamis dan pengumpulan sampah. Ini mendukung beberapa paradigma pemrograman, termasuk pemrograman terstruktur (terutama, prosedural), berorientasi objek, dan fungsional. Python sering dideskripsikan sebagai bahasa "termasuk baterai" karena perpustakaan standarnya yang komprehensif. Python dibuat pada akhir 1980-an sebagai penerus . Python 2.0, dirilis pada tahun 2000, memperkenalkan fitur-fitur seperti dan sistem pengumpulan sampah dengan . Python 3.0, dirilis pada tahun 2008, adalah revisi utama dari bahasa yang tidak sepenuhnya dengan versi sebelumnya, dan banyak kode Python 2 yang tidak berjalan tanpa modifikasi pada Python 3. Penerjemah Python tersedia untuk banyak sistem operasi. Komunitas pemrogram global mengembangkan dan memelihara CPython, implementasi referensi yang bebas dan sumber terbuka. Sebuah organisasi nirlaba, , mengelola dan mengarahkan sumber daya untuk pengembangan Python dan CPython. Python secara konsisten menempati peringkat sebagai salah satu bahasa pemrograman paling populer.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python is a high-level, general-purpose programming language. Its design philosophy emphasizes code readability with the use of significant indentation. Python is dynamically-typed and garbage-collected. It supports multiple programming paradigms, including structured (particularly procedural), object-oriented and functional programming. It is often described as a "batteries included" language due to its comprehensive standard library. Guido van Rossum began working on Python in the late 1980s as a successor to the ABC programming language and first released it in 1991 as Python 0.9.0. Python 2.0 was released in 2000 and introduced new features such as list comprehensions, cycle-detecting garbage collection, reference counting, and Unicode support. Python 3.0, released in 2008, was a major revision that is not completely backward-compatible with earlier versions. Python 2 was discontinued with version 2.7.18 in 2020. Python consistently ranks as one of the most popular programming languages.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python (prononc /pi.t/) est un langage de programmation interprt, multiparadigme et multiplateformes. Il favorise la programmation imprative structure, fonctionnelle et oriente objet. Il est dot d'un typage dynamique fort, d'une gestion automatique de la mmoire par ramasse-miettes et d'un systme de gestion d'exceptions ; il est ainsi similaire  Perl, Ruby, Scheme, Smalltalk et Tcl. Le langage Python est plac sous une licence libre proche de la licence BSD et fonctionne sur la plupart des plateformes informatiques, des smartphones aux ordinateurs centraux, de Windows  Unix avec notamment GNU/Linux en passant par macOS, ou encore Android, iOS, et peut aussi tre traduit en Java ou .NET. Il est conu pour optimiser la productivit des programmeurs en offrant des outils de haut niveau et une syntaxe simple  utiliser. Il est galement apprci par certains pdagogues qui y trouvent un langage o la syntaxe, clairement spare des mcanismes de bas niveau, permet une initiation aise aux concepts de base de la programmation.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python  un linguaggio di programmazione di "alto livello", orientato a oggetti, adatto, tra gli altri usi, a sviluppare applicazioni distribuite, scripting, computazione numerica e system testing. Ideato da Guido van Rossum all'inizio degli anni novanta,  spesso paragonato a Ruby, Tcl, Perl, JavaScript, Visual Basic o Scheme. Il nome fu scelto per la passione dello stesso inventore verso i Monty Python e per la loro serie televisiva Monty Python's Flying Circus. Spesso viene anche studiato tra i primi linguaggi per la sua somiglianza a uno pseudo-codice e di frequente viene usato per simulare la creazione di software grazie alla flessibilit di sperimentazione consentita da Python, che permette al programmatore di organizzare le idee durante lo sviluppo, come per esempio il creare un gioco tramite Pygame oppure il back-end di un sito web tramite Flask o Django. Python dispone anche di una sezione grafica, il modulo Python Turtle Graphics, che permette di applicare le righe di codici alla grafica.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python is een programmeertaal die begin jaren 90 ontworpen en ontwikkeld werd door Guido van Rossum, destijds verbonden aan het Centrum voor Wiskunde en Informatica (daarvoor Mathematisch Centrum) in Amsterdam. De taal is mede gebaseerd op inzichten van professor Lambert Meertens, die de programmeertaal ABC ontworpen had, bedoeld als alternatief voor BASIC, maar dan met geavanceerde datastructuren. Inmiddels wordt de taal doorontwikkeld door een enthousiaste groep, tot juli 2018 geleid door Van Rossum. Deze groep wordt ondersteund door vrijwilligers op het internet. De Python Software Foundation leidt de ontwikkeling van Python. Python is vrije software. Python dankt zijn naam aan het favoriete televisieprogramma van Guido van Rossum, Monty Python's Flying Circus.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python  jzyk programowania wysokiego poziomu oglnego przeznaczenia, o rozbudowanym pakiecie bibliotek standardowych, ktrego ide przewodni jest czytelno i klarowno kodu rdowego. Jego skadnia cechuje si przejrzystoci i zwizoci. Python wspiera rne paradygmaty programowania: obiektowy, imperatywny oraz w mniejszym stopniu funkcyjny. Posiada w peni dynamiczny system typw i automatyczne zarzdzanie pamici, bdc w tym podobnym do jzykw Perl, Ruby, Scheme czy Tcl. Podobnie jak inne jzyki dynamiczne jest czsto uywany jako jzyk skryptowy. Interpretery Pythona s dostpne na wiele systemw operacyjnych. Python rozwijany jest jako projekt Open Source zarzdzany przez Python Software Foundation, ktra jest organizacj non-profit. Standardow implementacj jzyka jest CPython (napisany w C), ale istniej te inne, np. Jython (napisany w Javie), CLPython napisany w Common Lisp, IronPython (na platform .NET) i PyPy (napisany w Pythonie, zob. ).

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python r ett programsprk som lanserades 1991 av Guido van Rossum. Det r vanligt som nybrjarsprk och inom undervisning, men ocks som generellt programsprk med tillmpning inom mnga olika domner. Det har dynamisk typning, varfr det ibland beskrivs som ett skriptsprk. Sprket utmrks ocks av att indentering pverkar programfldet. Detta gr programkoden kompakt och anses ge den god lsbarhet. Sprket utvecklas som ppen kllkod. Till sprket hr drfr flera utvecklingsmiljer, ett rikt standardbibliotek och mnga tredjepartsbibliotek. Dessa har tillmpningsomrden inom textbehandling, datorgrafik, spelprogrammering, datavisualisering, vetenskapliga berkningar, maskininlrning, datamining, grafiska anvndargrnssnitt, webbserverscript, systemautomation/skalskript och programmering av mikrokontroller/inbyggda system. Version Python 3.0, som slpptes 2008, var en strre versyn av sprket som inte r baktkompatibel, men mycket kod fr den sista tidigare versionen Python 2.7.18 och tidigare har levt kvar lnge.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Python_(programming_language)
object: Python  uma linguagem de programao de alto nvel, interpretada de script, imperativa, orientada a objetos, funcional, de tipagem dinmica e forte. Foi lanada por Guido van Rossum em 1991. Atualmente, possui um modelo de desenvolvimento comunitrio, aberto e gerenciado pela organizao sem fins lucrativos Python Software Foundation. Apesar de vrias partes da linguagem possurem padres e especificaes formais, a linguagem, como um todo, no  formalmente especificada. O padro na pratica  a implementao CPython. A linguagem foi projetada com a filosofia de enfatizar a importncia do esforo do programador sobre o esforo computacional. Prioriza a legibilidade do cdigo sobre a velocidade ou expressividade. Combina uma sintaxe concisa e clara com os recursos poderosos de sua biblioteca padro e por mdulos e frameworks desenvolvidos por terceiros. Python  uma linguagem de propsito geral de alto nvel, multiparadigma, suporta o paradigma orientado a objetos, imperativo, funcional e procedural. Possui tipagem dinmica e uma de suas principais caractersticas  permitir a fcil leitura do cdigo e exigir poucas linhas de cdigo se comparado ao mesmo programa em outras linguagens. Devido s suas caractersticas, ela  utilizada, principalmente, para processamento de textos, dados cientficos e criao de CGIs para pginas dinmicas para a web. Foi considerada pelo pblico a 3 linguagem "mais amada", de acordo com uma pesquisa conduzida pelo site Stack Overflow em 2018 e est entre as 5 linguagens mais populares, de acordo com uma pesquisa conduzida pela RedMonk. O nome Python teve a sua origem no grupo humorstico britnico Monty Python, criador do programa Monty Python's Flying Circus, embora muitas pessoas faam associao com o rptil do mesmo nome (em portugus, pton ou pito).

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qore_(programming_language)
object: Qore is an interpreted, high-level, general-purpose, garbage collected dynamic programming language, featuring support for code embedding and sandboxing with optional strong typing and a focus on fundamental support for multithreading and SMP scalability. Qore is unique because it is an interpreted scripting language with fundamental support for multithreading (meaning more than one part of the same code can run at the same time), and additionally because it features automatic memory management (meaning programmers do not have to allocate and free memory explicitly) while also supporting the RAII idiom with destructors for scope-based resource management and exception-safe programming. This is due to Qore's unique prompt collection implementation for garbage collection.

subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qore_(programming_language)
object: Qore  uma linguagem de programao dinmica interpretada, de alto nvel, de uso geral, com colector de lixo e com capacidade para incorporao de cdigo e isolamento de processos com tipificao forte opcional. Tambm permite mltiplos fios de execuo e escalabilidade de multiprocessamento simtrico (SMP). A linguagem Qore  nica porque  uma linguagem interpretada com capacidade para mltiplos fios de execuo (o que significa que mais do que uma parte do mesmo cdigo pode ser executada ao mesmo tempo), tem gesto automtica de memria (ou seja, os programadores no precisam de reservar e libertar memria explicitamente),  compatvel com o padro RAII (Aquisio de Recurso  Inicializao) atravs de destrutores para gesto de recursos baseada em alcance e permite programao com segurana no tratamento de excepes. Isto deve-se  implementao exclusiva de colecta pronta, ou colecta de lixo determinstica, da linguagem Qore.
